article.description: Sheri Sam scored a career-high 27 points to help the Miami Sol end a four-game losing streak with a 78-74 overtime victory that kept the Detroit Shock winless.
article.headline: Sol need OT to end their four-game skid
article.linkText: Sam's career high helps Sol hold off winless Shock
article.story:
AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) -- Sheri Sam scored a career-high 27 points to help the Miami Sol end a four-game losing streak with a 78-74 overtime victory that kept the Detroit Shock winless.

Reserve Betty Lennox scored 17 points, including a go-ahead
jumper to give the Sol (3-9) a 76-74 lead with 3:15 left in
overtime. The Shock dropped to a WNBA-worst 0-13.

"It was a funny game statistically,'' Sam said. "They outscored us 30-5 from the line and outrebounded us (43-25), but the biggest difference was our heart and not giving up.''

Detroit made 30 of 39 free throws. Shock rookie forward Swin
Cash set franchise records for free throws made (15) and attempted
(21), but she missed two with 2:22 left in overtime and the Shock
trailing 76-74. Cash finished with 17 points.

   "Miami made some big plays in clutch situations and Sam got red
hot,'' said Shock Coach Bill Laimbeer, 0-3 since replacing Greg
Williams. "We did what we were supposed to do except for the final
score. We wanted to attack the basket and get to the line, and we
did just that.

"Swin Cash is our primary weapon in transition, and she's good
at getting to the line. That's her job.''

The Shock turned the ball over 22 times compared to Miami's
eight turnovers. The Sol shot 42.3 percent from the field, the
Shock 38.5 percent.

Detroit led 35-31 at halftime, outscoring Miami 17-1 from the
line, but Sam scored 10 points in a 3:08 span, including two
3-pointers, to help turn a 39-37 deficit into a 47-41 lead.

Debbie Black had 12 points and six assists for the Sol.
Pollyanna Johns Kimbrough had five points and seven rebounds. She
made two free throws for the game's final points. Kristen Rasmussen
had eight points for Miami.

Wendy Palmer had 13 points and nine rebounds for the Shock, and
Ayana Walker added 11 points. Dominique Canty had eight assists.
